title: Arkansas' Greenlaw is SEC Freshman of the Week
text:
Arkansas’ Greenlaw is SEC Freshman of the Week By - Associated Press   
FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. (AP) - University of Arkansas freshman linebacker Dre Greenlaw has been named the Southeastern Conference Freshman of the Week. 
Greenlaw was announced Monday as the winner of the award after making 16 tackles during the Razorbacks’ four-overtime win over Auburn. 
Greenlaw made 12 of the tackles during the second half and the overtime as Arkansas beat Auburn 54-46.
